Indiana State Road 312 - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia Indiana State Road 312 From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia   (Redirected from Indiana State Highway 312) Jump to: navigation, search State Road 312 Length: 5.7 mi[1] (9.2 km) West end: South Brainard Avenue & South State Line Road at the Illinois state line East end: SR 912 in East Chicago[2] Counties: Lake Indiana roads < SR 311 SR 327 > Interstates - U.S. Routes - State Roads - Former State Road 312 in the U.S. state of Indiana is an east-west state highway in Indiana. It runs from the Illinois state line east to SR 912. in East Chicago. At one point, it used to continue for less than a mile east of SR 912 to end at U.S. Route 12. This is a distance of 5.7 miles (9.2 km).[1] This state road is primarily local in nature, serving an industrial area of East Chicago and allowing easy access to Cline Avenue. Indiana 312 is called Chicago Avenue for most of the eastern 5 miles (8.0 km). It turns north onto Sheffield Avenue and west onto Gostlin Street before becoming Brainard Avenue in Illinois. [edit] References ^ a b Indiana Highway Ends - SR 312 ^ Indiana Department of Transportation. "Indiana GIS Atlas". http://129.79.145.7/arcims/statewide_mxd/index.html. Retrieved on 2008-01-03.  This Indiana road or road transport-related article is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it. Retrieved from "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indiana_State_Road_312" Categories: State highways in Indiana | Indiana road stubs Views Article Discussion Edit this page History Personal tools Log in / create account Navigation Main page Contents Featured content Current events Random article Search   Interaction About Wikipedia Community portal Recent changes Contact Wikipedia Donate to Wikipedia Help Toolbox What links here Related changes Upload file Special pages Printable version Permanent link Cite this page This page was last modified on 9 February 2009, at 09:45. All text is available under the terms of the GNU Free Docume